To register as an administrator, an applicant must present evidence satisfactory to the Commissioner that the applicant:
has not been convicted of:
a felony;
a misdemeanor involving moral turpitude;
a violation of this subtitle;
an attempt or conspiracy to commit any of the violations listed in subitems (i) through (iii) of this item; or
a crime in which any other violation listed in this item is an element;
has obtained the bond required by § 8-306 of this subtitle or has qualified for one of the applicable exemptions from the bonding requirement;
has met any applicable examination requirements adopted by the Commissioner under subsection (b) of this section; and
for the administration of health benefit plans in the State, uses only the uniform claim forms adopted by the Commissioner under § 15-1003 of this article.
